<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-02-0387 </DOCNO><TEXT>This collection of five papers on molten salts deals with the followingspecific topics: the actinides and their salts, including their availabilityalong with techniques and equipment for their handling, preparation,purification, and physical property measurement; cryolite systems andmethods for their handling, preparation, and thermodynamic and physicochemicalproperty assessment, as well as the use of electrodes in molten cryolite;the theory, construction, and application of reference electrodes formolten salt electrolytes; neutron diffraction in molten salt systemsincluding isotope exchange methods for sample preparation; and dry boxesand inert atmosphere techniques for molten salt handling and analysis.</TEXT></DOC>